## 7. DATA RETENTION SCHEDULE

### 7.1 By Data Type

**Account Information (Name, Email, Phone, Password Hash)**
- **Retention:** While account is active
- **After deletion:** 30 days (recovery period if accidental deletion)
- **Then:** Permanently deleted
- **Exception:** Anonymized data kept for analytics (cannot identify you)

**Payment & Transaction Data**
- **Retention:** 7 years from transaction date
- **Why:** Indian income tax law requires 7-year record retention
- **Format:** Anonymized (no personal identifiers except reference ID)
- **After 7 years:** Completely deleted

**Video Content & Campaign Data**
- **Retention:** While campaign is active + 30 days after
- **Why:** Dispute resolution and quality assurance
- **Creator option:** Can download videos during 30-day window
- **After 30 days:** Deleted from Platform (Creator retains ownership)
- **Note:** Brand retains license to use video (perpetual)

**Email Communications**
- **Retention:** 1 year or until support ticket closed (whichever longer)
- **Why:** Audit trail for disputes
- **Then:** Deleted
- **Exception:** Dispute records kept 7 years

**Order Proof Screenshots**
- **Retention:** 30 days after campaign completion
- **Why:** Proof in case of disputes
- **Then:** Deleted

**Marketing & Newsletter Preferences**
- **Retention:** Until you unsubscribe
- **Unsubscribe:** Click link in email or email support@brandklip.com
- **Then:** Email deleted from marketing list

**Analytics & Usage Data (Anonymized)**
- **Retention:** 26 months (Google Analytics)
- **Then:** Auto-deleted by Google

**Cookies**
- **Session cookies:** Deleted when you log out
- **Analytics cookies:** 1 year
- **Clear cookies:** Browser settings → Clear cache

